## Ingredients

- [ ] 2 Tbsp Olive Oil or Butter
- [ ] 1 medium Onion, diced
- [ ] 2 cloves Garlic, minced
- [ ] 2 medium Potatoes, diced into 1/2 inch cubes
- [ ] 1/4 head Red Cabbage, thinly sliced (about 2-3 cups)
- [ ] 1/2 tsp Paprika
- [ ] 1/2 tsp Salt
- [ ] 1/4 tsp Black Pepper
- [ ] (Optional) 4 Eggs for topping
- [ ] (Optional) Fresh herbs like Parsley or Chives for garnish
- [ ] (Optional) Hot sauce for serving

## Recipe

1. Heat 1 Tbsp oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat
1. Add diced potatoes and cook for 8-10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until golden and tender
1. Push potatoes to the side and add remaining 1 Tbsp oil
1. Add onion and cook for 3-4 minutes until softened
1. Add garlic and cook for 30 seconds until fragrant
1. Add sliced red cabbage, paprika, salt, and pepper. Stir everything together
1. Cook for 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is tender and lightly caramelized
1. If using eggs, make 4 wells in the hash and crack an egg into each well
1. Cover and cook for 3-5 minutes until eggs are set to your liking
1. Garnish with fresh herbs and serve with hot sauce if desired

## Notes

- Sweet potatoes work well as a substitute for regular potatoes
- Add cooked sausage or bacon for extra protein
- Can meal prep the hash without eggs and reheat throughout the week
- The red cabbage will turn a beautiful purple color as it cooks
